  <h1 id="exemptions"><%= @title %> <a href="#exemptions">#</a></h1>

  <p>Under <a href="https://www.access.gov.hk/en/codeonacctoinfo/part2.html">Part 2 of the Code on Access to Information</a>, departments may refuse to disclose information, or may refuse to confirm or deny the existence of information, in certain categories.</p>

  <p><strong>Important:</strong> When refusing a request, departments must quote the relevant paragraph(s) from Part 2 and provide appropriate elaboration. In many cases, departments must also consider whether the <strong>public interest</strong> in disclosure outweighs any harm or prejudice.</p>

  <h2 id="categories">The 16 Exemption Categories <a href="#categories">#</a></h2>

  <dl>
    <dt id="defence_security">1. Defence, Security and External Affairs <a href="#defence_security">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure would:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Harm or prejudice Hong Kong's <strong>defence or security</strong></li>
        <li>Harm the conduct of <strong>external affairs</strong> or relations with other governments or international organisations</li>
        <li>Endanger the <strong>life or physical safety</strong> of any person</li>
        <li>Identify sources of information given in confidence for security or law enforcement purposes</li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="law_order">2. Law Enforcement and Legal Proceedings <a href="#law_order">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure would:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Prejudice the <strong>prevention or detection of crime</strong></li>
        <li>Harm the <strong>apprehension or prosecution</strong> of offenders</li>
        <li>Prejudice the <strong>administration of justice</strong></li>
        <li>Result in the <strong>disclosure of confidential sources</strong> of information for law enforcement</li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="immigration">3. Immigration and Prison Matters <a href="#immigration">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure would:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Prejudice the <strong>effective administration</strong> of immigration control</li>
        <li>Harm the security of <strong>correctional institutions</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="public_safety">4. Public Safety <a href="#public_safety">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure would:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Endanger the <strong>safety of any person or property</strong></li>
        <li>Facilitate unlawful interference with systems or property</li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="environment">5. Environment <a href="#environment">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure would:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Increase the likelihood of <strong>damage to the environment</strong></li>
        <li>Harm <strong>rare or endangered species</strong> and their habitats</li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="economic">6. Economic Management <a href="#economic">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure would:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Harm or prejudice the conduct of <strong>monetary policy</strong></li>
        <li>Harm the maintenance of <strong>stability in financial markets</strong></li>
        <li>Prejudice the Government's ability to <strong>manage the economy</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="management">7. Management and Operations of Government <a href="#management">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure would:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Harm or prejudice the <strong>proper and efficient conduct</strong> of government operations</li>
        <li>Prejudice the <strong>effective formulation</strong> of policy</li>
        <li>Harm <strong>fair and effective management</strong> of personnel</li>
        <li>Prejudice the conduct of <strong>contractual or other negotiations</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="premature">8. Premature Disclosure <a href="#premature">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure would be <strong>premature</strong> because:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The information relates to <strong>incomplete analysis</strong></li>
        <li>The information relates to <strong>tentative policy proposals</strong></li>
        <li>Disclosure before completion would be <strong>misleading or harmful</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="law_enforcement_info">9. Law Enforcement Information <a href="#law_enforcement_info">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information obtained or prepared for <strong>law enforcement purposes</strong> may be refused if disclosure would:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Identify a confidential source</li>
        <li>Reveal investigative techniques</li>
        <li>Prejudice ongoing or future law enforcement activities</li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="legal_restrictions">10. Legal Restrictions <a href="#legal_restrictions">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure is:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Prohibited or restricted by <strong>law or regulation</strong></li>
        <li>Subject to <strong>legal professional privilege</strong></li>
        <li>Protected by <strong>statutory provisions</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="privacy">11. Privacy and Confidentiality <a href="#privacy">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure would:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Constitute an <strong>unwarranted invasion of personal privacy</strong></li>
        <li>Breach a <strong>duty of confidence</strong> owed to any person</li>
        <li>Violate confidentiality provisions</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Note:</strong> For your own personal information, make a Data Access Request under the <a href="https://www.pcpd.org.hk/">Personal Data (Privacy) Ordinance</a> instead.</p>
    </dd>

    <dt id="commercial">12. Commercial Interests <a href="#commercial">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure would:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Harm or prejudice <strong>commercial interests</strong></li>
        <li>Prejudice <strong>competitive position</strong> of parties</li>
        <li>Interfere with <strong>contractual or other negotiations</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="research">13. Research and Innovation <a href="#research">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure would:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Inhibit the free and frank provision of <strong>advice or exchange of views</strong></li>
        <li>Prejudice the conduct of <strong>research or analysis</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="utilities">14. Public Utilities <a href="#utilities">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Information may be refused if disclosure would:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Prejudice the <strong>safe operation</strong> of public utilities</li>
        <li>Increase security risks to <strong>essential infrastructure</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </dd>

    <dt id="public_interest">15. Public Interest Test <a href="#public_interest">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>For many exemptions, departments must conduct a <strong>public interest test</strong>:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Consider whether the harm from disclosure outweighs the public interest in transparency</li>
        <li>Balance competing interests</li>
        <li>Document the reasoning for the decision</li>
      </ul>
      <p>If you believe the public interest favors disclosure, make this argument in your request or internal review.</p>
    </dd>

    <dt id="vexatious">16. Vexatious or Repeated Requests <a href="#vexatious">#</a></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>Departments may refuse requests that are:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Vexatious</strong> - made to harass or cause annoyance</li>
        <li><strong>Substantially similar</strong> to previous requests by the same requester</li>
        <li><strong>Unreasonably voluminous</strong> or would require disproportionate effort</li>
      </ul>
    </dd>
  </dl>

  <h2 id="challenging">Challenging a Refusal <a href="#challenging">#</a></h2>

  <p>If your request is refused and you believe the refusal is unjustified:</p>

  <ol>
    <li><strong>Request an internal review</strong> - Ask a senior officer in the department to review the decision</li>
    <li><strong>Complain to The Ombudsman</strong> - If the internal review is unsatisfactory, lodge a complaint with <a href="https://www.ombudsman.hk/">The Ombudsman (申訴專員)</a></li>
    <li><strong>Refine your request</strong> - Consider narrowing your request or asking for summary information that may not be exempt</li>
  </ol>

  <p>Read more about <a href="<%= help_general_path(:template => 'unhappy') %>">what to do if you're unhappy with a response</a>.</p>

